## <a id='overview'></a> Overview

To simplify APM setup, the [AppDynamics Application Performance Monitoring (APM) for VMware Tanzu](https://network.pivotal.io/products/p-appdynamics/) (VMware Tanzu) tile delivers a service broker to support an AppDynamics marketplace service. The Controller parameters are configured in the tile and automatically published to the marketplace when the tile is installed.

A VMware Tanzu app can be bound to the marketplace service to consume the Controller credentials.

````
$ cf bind-service my-pcf-app my-appd-marketplace-service
````

Performing a push will utilize the integrated AppDynamics buildpack support to start the APM agent based on the parameters from the marketplace service and start sending performance metrics to the Controller.

````
$ cf push
````

The tile also installs the AppDynamics extension buildpack in the VMware Tanzu environment. For more information see the [buildpack support](https://docs.pivotal.io/partners/appdynamics/multibuildpack.html) and [language-specific workflows](https://docs.pivotal.io/partners/appdynamics/using.html#workflows) sections to enable APM.


